{"product_id":"shield-blend","title":"Shield Blend","description":"\u003cp\u003eShield Blend (Thieves) is a mixture of undiluted, 100% pure, USDA certified organic essential oils of Clove Bud, Lemon, Cinnamon Bark, Eucalyptus Radiata, and Rosemary. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCultivation Method: \u003c\/strong\u003eUSDA Certified Organic\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eApproximate Shelf Life: \u003c\/strong\u003e﻿1 – 2 years\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMax dilution: \u003c\/strong\u003e0.45%\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cu\u003eRecommended Usage\u003c\/u\u003e\u003c\/strong\u003e\u003c\/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSee our \u003cu\u003eGeneral Safety Guidelines\u003c\/u\u003e for recommended usage.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis oil \u003cstrong\u003eis not safe\u003c\/strong\u003e for children.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis blend is great for a variety of skin issues including eczema, psoriasis, boils, pimples, warts, acne, athlete’s foot, and others.  It also helps fight signs of aging with powerful antioxidants and by improving elasticity.  It is an effective aid in a range respiratory issues from cough and congestion to bacterial and viral infections.  It also supports the immune system and aids digestion.  It will help prevent cuts and wounds from becoming infected as well as speed the healing process.  It is also great for dental health, allergies, cold sores, pain relief, insect bites and stings, and Lyme disease.  On top of all this, it can help ease stress and anxiety.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAround the house the oil can be used to sanitize, remove odors, purify the air, remove adhesives, and destroy mold.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdd a maximum of \u003cstrong\u003e1 drop \u003c\/strong\u003e(0.05 mL) \u003cstrong\u003eto 10 mL of carrier oil \u003c\/strong\u003e(or 0.45%) for topical applications.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eApply mixture and rub into skin on desired area, wrists, neck, abdomen, or during massage.  Avoid freshly broken skin, eyes, and sensitive areas.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cu\u003eSafety and Warnings\u003c\/u\u003e\u003c\/strong\u003e\u003c\/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShield Blend oil can cause CNS and breathing problems in young children, therefore, avoid use on or near the face of children under 2 years of age.  This oil can interact (through oral routes) with pethidine, MAOIs, indirect sympathomimetics, SSRIs, medications treating blood clotting, major surgery, peptic ulcer, hemophilia, and other bleeding disorders.  Avoid using on diseased or damaged skin or if hypersensitive.  This oil may be oil may be embryotoxic and inhibit blood clotting.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis oil can be phototoxic and should not be used topically above concentrations of 6.8% on areas of skin that will be exposed to sunlight in the next 12 hours. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBelow are some potential drug interactions for Shield Blend.  \u003cem\u003eCheck with your healthcare provider before using Shield Blend essential oil if you are currently taking prescription medication.\u003c\/em\u003e\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eModerate interaction:\u003c\/strong\u003e\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDiabetes medications (Antidiabetic drugs) such as Amaryl, glyburide (DiaBeta, Glynase PresTab, Micronase), insulin, Actos, Avandia, Diabinese, Glucotrol, Orinase and others.\u003c\/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedications that slow blood clotting (Anticoagulant\/Antiplatelet drugs) such as aspirin, clopidogrel (Plavix), diclofenac (Voltaren, Cataflam, others), ibuprofen (Advil, Motrin, others), naproxen (Anaprox, Naprosyn, others), dalteparin (Fragmin), enoxaparin (Lovenox), heparin, warfarin (Coumadin), and others.\u003c\/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVerteporfin – effectiveness is reduced.\u003c\/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMAOIs 